        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): surface multi-account default routing warnings in preview and lint",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nFixes an issue where `openclaw doctor` preview and `openclaw doctor --lint` did not surface warnings about multi-account channels that lack explicit default routing or complete account-scoped bindings. Operators could not discover ambiguous routing configurations without running a full doctor run.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nSurface `collectMissingDefaultAccountBindingWarnings` and `collectMissingExplicitDefaultAccountWarnings` in the lightweight preview/lint paths, so operators get routing warnings early without waiting for a full doctor run. The new `core/doctor/default-account-routing` check is registered in the ordered doctor contributions so `runDoctorLintCli` schedules it.\n\n## User Impact\nOperators running `openclaw doctor` preview or `openclaw doctor --lint` now see warnings when multi-account channels lack explicit default routing.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Vitest:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  48 passed (48)\n```\n\n**Contribution registration fix (P1):** `core/doctor/default-account-routing` added to `doctor:gateway-services` healthCheckIds.\n\n**What was not tested:** Full `openclaw doctor --lint` CLI output (requires gateway with multi-account channel configuration).",
